&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Legacy at North Augusta – Where CNAs Shine and Brighten Lives Every Day!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Title:&lt;/strong&gt; Certified Nursing Assistant (CNA)&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Type:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Full-time&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Shift:&lt;/strong&gt; Day&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Pay Range:&lt;/strong&gt; $18.50- $23.50 an/hour &lt;em&gt;(Final offer based on your unique skills, experience, and professional background)&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At The Legacy at North Augusta, a proud member of the National Lutheran Service family, we believe that exceptional care starts with exceptional people. As a CNA here, you’ll empower residents to live with dignity and independence, making a genuine impact each day through your compassion, respect, and unwavering dedication. Every shift offers a new opportunity to create meaningful connections and deliver comfort, compassion, and outstanding care to those who need it most.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why You’ll Love Being Part of Our Team&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Make a Real Impact: Help seniors maintain their independence and thrive.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Feel Truly Valued:&amp;nbsp;Join a supportive, appreciative team that recognizes your dedication.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Enjoy Flexibility:&amp;nbsp;Choose shifts that fit your schedule—perfect for balancing work and life.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Grow Your Career:&amp;nbsp;Access ongoing training and professional development.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work in a Positive Culture:&amp;nbsp;Experience respect, teamwork, and genuine appreciation every day.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support residents with daily living activities—bathing, dressing, grooming, and more&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor and record vital signs (blood pressure, temperature, pulse)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with mobility and safe transfers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare and serve meals tailored to residents needs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Communicate clearly with clients, families, and care team members&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Observe and promptly report changes in residents’ condition&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What We’re Looking For:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Active CNA certification in Virginia in good standing&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Passion for providing compassionate, resident-focused care&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong teamwork skills and a positive attitude&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Commitment to maintaining a professional, respectful environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Compassionate, dependable, and patient&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Physical ability to assist with client transfers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As part of National Lutheran Communities and Services, we offer great PERKS and BENEFITS to promote a better quality of life for our team members.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Our Comprehensive Benefits Include:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Competitive pay with night shift differential&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Earn up to 5 weeks of PTO in your first year!&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;403(b) retirement plan with employer matching&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Medical, dental, and vision insurance plans&lt;/li&gt;
