&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Village at Orchard Ridge – Where Service Excellence Meets Purpose and Community!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Title:&lt;/strong&gt; EVS Supervisor (Environmental Services Supervisor)&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Type:&lt;/strong&gt; Full Time&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Shift:&lt;/strong&gt; Day&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Salary Range:&lt;/strong&gt; &amp;nbsp;$22.00 - $28.00/hour, with final offer based on skills, experience, and background.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At The Village at Orchard Ridge, we understand that a clean and welcoming environment is essential for our residents, guests, and staff alike. As an EVS Supervisor, you will play a vital leadership role in ensuring our community spaces are maintained to the highest standards. This position is ideal for someone who leads by example, inspires teamwork, and is passionate about making a positive impact within a purpose-driven organization.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why You’ll Appreciate Joining Our Team&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Meaningful Contribution: Shape the cleanliness, safety, and overall experience of our vibrant community.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Team-Focused Environment: Collaborate with supportive colleagues who value respect, open communication, and partnership.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Leadership Development: Access opportunities for growth through training, certifications, and advancement pathways.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Dynamic Workdays: Enjoy a varied role where every shift offers new challenges and meaningful work.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comprehensive Benefits: Receive a competitive salary and a range of valuable benefits that reward your dedication.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What We’re Seeking&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;High school graduate or equivalent education is required, some college is preferred&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Must have positive supervisory skills with a minimum of two (2) years’ supervisory experience preferred, environmental services experience preferred, including supervising teams with proven success&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge of and proficiency in the practices and procedures of environmental services; must be familiar with the use of detergents, germicides, strippers and other cleaning/chemical supplies&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiar with common environmental service equipment; able to troubleshoot equipment malfunctions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Must be familiar with common environmental services practices, infection control procedures, pest control programs and floor maintenance methods&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to read, write and follow direct written and oral instructions in English Ability to communicate at all levels, provide instruction, coach and train team members&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Must understand and own staff scheduling process&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Operational Excellence &amp;amp; Team Leadership&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manages environmental, housekeeping and laundry activities so that optimal services are provided in an efficient and effective manner, may oversee security at specific communities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Supervises and manages all environmental services team members including assigning daily work responsibilities&lt;/li&gt;
