&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why You’ll Love Working Nights with Us&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Peaceful Environment: Enjoy a calm, steady pace that allows for deeper connections with residents.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Autonomy and Trust: Use your clinical judgment and expertise in a collaborative, supportive setting.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong Team Culture: Work alongside caring RNs, dedicated caregivers, and engaged leadership who appreciate your unique contributions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Competitive Pay: Benefit from shift differentials and pay that honors your commitment and skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Purpose-Filled Nights: Make every hour count by providing compassionate, one-on-one care that improves lives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide direct nursing care consistent with physicians’ orders and individual care plans.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Administer medications and treatments with accuracy and compassion.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor residents’ health, ensuring timely communication of changes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Keep detailed, accurate clinical records.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with residents, families, and team members to promote holistic well-being.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support safety and infection control protocols with care and attention.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What We’re Looking For&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Current LPN license in the state of Virginia.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;1 year of nursing experience in a hospital, long-term care, or related setting.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A heart for serving older adults with dignity and compassion.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong communication, reliability, and teamwork skills.&lt;/li&gt;
